From: Carlos Munoz <cmunoz@caviumnetworks.com>
Date: Wed, 2 Jul 2014 18:05:50 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 937/974] netdev: octeon3-ethernet: Allow user to change
 settings.

Signed-off-by: Carlos Munoz <cmunoz@caviumnetworks.com>
[Original patch taken from Cavium SDK 3.1.2-568]
Signed-off-by: Quanyang Wang <quanyang.wang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/octeon/octeon3-ethernet.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/octeon/octeon3-ethernet.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/octeon/octeon3-ethernet.c
index 1e90abb..e5cca23 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/octeon/octeon3-ethernet.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/octeon/octeon3-ethernet.c
@@ -1486,6 +1486,9 @@ static int octeon3_eth_common_ndo_init(struct net_device	*netdev,
 	if (octeon_has_feature(OCTEON_FEATURE_TSO))
 		netdev->features |= NETIF_F_TSO | NETIF_F_TSO6;
 
+	/* Set user changable settings */
+	netdev->hw_features = netdev->features;
+
 	priv->rx_buf_count = num_packet_buffers;
 
 	ipd_port = cvmx_helper_get_ipd_port(priv->xiface, priv->port_index);
